==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prelect
<hw>Pre*lect"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Prelected</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Prelecting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>praelectus</ets>, p.
p. of <ets>praelegere</ets> to read before. See <er>Pre-</er>, and
<er>Lection</er>.]</ety> <def>To read publicly, as a lecture or
discourse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prelect</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Prelect
<hw>Pre*lect"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To discourse publicly; to
lecture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Spitting . . . was publicly <qex>prelected</qex> upon.</q>
<rj><qau>De. Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To <qex>prelect</qex> upon the military art.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Horsley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prelection</ent>⟦br⟧
